# Building an iOS App using Python

## Task Description

In this task, you will learn how to build an iOS app using Python. While Python is not a native iOS development language, we can utilize a tool called KIVY to help us achieve this. KIVY is an open-source library that enables the creation of cross-platform apps using Python.

## Task Objectives

1. Understand the basics of KIVY framework.
2. Set up a development environment for building iOS apps with Python.
3. Create a simple iOS app using Python and KIVY.

## Resources

- [KIVY Documentation](https://kivy.org/doc/stable/)

## Answer:
-To build an iOS app using Python, you can utilize the Kivy framework.
Kivy is an open-source Python library that enables the creation of cross-platform mobile applications
including those for iOS. Keep in mind that Python is not a native iOS development language 
so Kivy acts as a bridge to facilitate this process.
